{"questionId":"15303594","questionHtml":"<p>By solving&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;simultaneously, show that these curves intersect at the points&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>at intersection,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to factorize either the LHS or the RHS of the first two equations above (or equivalent) OR attempts to partially factorize the LHS side of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M</strong><strong>1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept alternative forms such as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>recognition that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent, e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>) (allows division by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Subsequent marks are not dependent on this <em><strong>R1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> As&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></math> is an <em><strong>AG</strong></em>, only award the above<em><strong> A1</strong></em> if&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> has been used.</p>\n<p>substitutes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;into either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and attempts to simplify&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M</strong><strong>1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15303594","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By solving y2=4a2-4ax and y2=4b2+4bx simultaneously, show that these curves intersect at the points Ma-b, 2ab and Na-b, -2ab.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}